Breeding male.description: Blue Grosbeaks are larger with a bigger and thicker bill than Indigo Buntings. Breeding males have rusty wingbars that Indigo Buntings do not have.

Female/immature.description: Blue Grosbeaks are larger than Indigo Buntings with a heavier bill. Females/immatures are a richer buffy brown with darker wingbars than female/immature Indigo Buntings.

Breeding male.description: Breeding male Lazuli Buntings are easily separated from male Indigo Buntings by their pumpkin colored chest.

Female/immature.description: On average female/immature Lazuli Buntings have bolder buffy wingbars and a warm unstreaked breast whereas female/immature Indigo Buntings often have faint streaking on the breast and a whiter throat.
Female Painted Buntings are distinctly greenish above, not buffy brown like female/immature Indigo Buntings.

Adult female.description: Eastern Bluebirds are larger birds with straight, thin bills unlike the thick conical bill of Indigo Buntings. They also have an orangish wash on the breast that Indigo Buntings lack.

Female.description: Female House Sparrows have a streaky back and a bolder, paler eyebrow than female/immature Indigo Buntings, which have an unstreaked back and a plain face.
